Asymmetrione nossibensis
— Madad, 2008: 2 , 5, 6, 16, 27, 28, 46, 47, 49, 51, 82, fig. 7F [ Philippines , infesting
Dardanus lagopodes (Forskål, 1775)
] (not
A . nossibensis Bourdon, 1976
).

A juvenile female (
Fig. 1C
) already shows the development of the lateral plates on the fifth pleomere but does not yet show the dorsal swellings on the pleotelson. This specimen also shows how the birfucated frontal lamina develops by a weak subdivision in the medial region that becomes progressively larger as the individual matures.
